<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-70-0599 </DOCNO><TEXT>It was earlier believed that quality and safety can only be achieved byextensive control. Today it is realized that faults cannot be avoidedby control alone. Nevertheless certain controls are necessary. The questionshould be asked: 'Where is it meaningful and economical to order andcarry out quality control?' The application of a risk assessment canhelp to answer this question. 10 refs., 6 figs., 6 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>